BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Native American/Alaskan Native Canoe Community Day
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20250927T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20250927T140000
DTSTAMP:20260424T230203Z
UID:4bb097a4-a49b-5d7a-99b8-a0ed6a64cc7b
DESCRIPTION:You are invited to Canoe Community Day on Saturday\, Septem
 ber 27th\, from 10:00 AM – 2:00 PM. Confluence\, Portland All Nations Ca
 noe Family\, and Lower Columbia Estuary Partnership are coming together to
  provide you with an opportunity to gather on the Tualatin River.Join us f
 or a day of connection on the Tualatin River\, where we’ll share space\,
  light food\, guided canoe tours\, and art activities led by Native educat
 ors and partnering educators.This event is open to all Hillsboro and Beav
 erton Title VI families. Life jackets will be provided for canoe tours. Ho
 wever\, please remember to bring sunscreen and wear clothing and shoes app
 ropriate for water activities.To ensure canoe space please register for th
 e day here by September 21st\, and arrive at 10am on September 27th.
LOCATION:17005 SW 92nd Ave. Tigard
END:VEVENT
