DTSTAMP:20260424T230203Z
UID:0e34dbb2-7676-5b5f-9ed9-41bd894bc4da
DESCRIPTION:The third annual Run for Hope\, recognizing and celebrating Do
 mestic Violence Awareness Month\, takes place on Sunday\, October 12\, fro
 m 10 a.m. to 1 p.m. at Hare Field. This family-friendly event offers a 5K 
 run/walk\, food trucks\, a DJ\, bouncy house\, face painting\, a resource 
 fair\, emergency vehicles to explore\, and more. The resource fair and kid
 s’ activities are free\, registration required for those participating
  in the 5K. 
LOCATION:Hare Field\, 1147 NE Grant St\, Hillsboro\, OR 97124
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:National School Lunch Week
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20251013
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20251018
DTSTAMP:20260424T230203Z
UID:26ff3e3c-62fc-5772-94fa-2c21a0e4cf3a
DESCRIPTION:National School Lunch Week is October 13-17 with a theme of 
 “Taste the World: Your School Lunch Passport!” School Lunch Week highl
 ights the importance of a healthy school lunch in a child’s life and the
  impact it has both in and out of the classroom. HSD is thrilled to be abl
 e to provide meals free of charge to all students. The National School Lu
 nch Program started in 1946 as a way to provide nutritious meals to childr
 en from low-income families who might not otherwise have access to a daily
  meal. President John F. Kennedy declared National School Lunch Week in 19
 62\, and now the school lunch program serves nearly 30 million children ev
 ery school day. Learn more at SchoolNutrition.org\, and check out our menu
  at LinqConnect.com (remember to select your school from the drop-down men
 u at the top of the page). 
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
