UID:520d41da-48e1-59b3-be37-e44adef56cba
DESCRIPTION:Día de los Muertos is a tradition with pre-Hispanic roots tha
 t commemorates ancestors and deceased family members. It’s a distinctive
  holiday that reunites the living and the dead\, and honors those we have 
 lost. Some of our schools will be setting up ofrendas\, and the City of Hi
 llsboro is hosting two events suitable for all ages: crafts and games at t
 he Shute Park Library from 2 p.m. to 5 p.m. on Saturday\, November 1\; and
  a celebration with Huecha Omeyocan at the Walters Cultural Arts Center fr
 om 5 p.m. to 8 p.m. on Tuesday\, November 4.
LOCATION:Shute Park Library\, 775 SE 10th Ave\, Hillsboro\, OR 97123
END:VEVENT
